docs.abstract: The police hoped that taking down online black markets would chase away criminals. But the amount of Bitcoin spent on illegal purposes has reached a new high.
docs.snippet: The police hoped that taking down online black markets would chase away criminals. But the amount of Bitcoin spent on illegal purposes has reached a new high.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — The last few months have not been good for Bitcoin. The value of the digital tokens has steadily dropped. Bitcoin trading on cryptocurrency exchanges has slowed. And using Bitcoin to buy legal items? That has also dropped.

headline.main: Bitcoin Has Lost Steam. But Criminals Still Love It.
headline.print_headline: Bitcoin Slump? Not in Criminal World

docs.abstract: The order formalizes a decision last year to ground the federal agency’s drones pending an internal security investigation.
docs.snippet: The order formalizes a decision last year to ground the federal agency’s drones pending an internal security investigation.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Interior Department announced on Wednesday that it was grounding its entire fleet of drones out of concerns that Chinese parts in them might be used for spying, making exceptions only for emergency missions like fighting wildfires and search-and-rescue operations.

headline.main: Interior Dept. Grounds Its Drones Over Chinese Spying Fears
headline.print_headline: Interior Dept. Halts Drones Over Worries About China

docs.abstract: Once wildly popular for its inexpensive, imported pillows and rattan chairs, the home furnishings chain struggled to compete against Home Goods and Etsy.
docs.snippet: Once wildly popular for its inexpensive, imported pillows and rattan chairs, the home furnishings chain struggled to compete against Home Goods and Etsy.
docs.lead_paragraph: Pier 1 Imports, the home goods retailer that in the 1990s became a popular destination for exotic rattan chairs and cheap embroidered pillows only to cede its market niche over the last decade to lower-priced competitors, announced on Monday that it had filed for bankruptcy and was pursuing a sale of the company.

headline.main: Pier 1 Imports, the Struggling Home Goods Retailer, Files for Bankruptcy
headline.print_headline: Pier 1 Imports Files for Bankruptcy After a Failed Attempt at a Turnaround
